---
description: Frontend feature module structure rules
globs:
  - "frontend/src/features/**"
  - "frontend/src/pages/**"
  - "frontend/src/core/**"
---

Keep frontend pages thin and feature modules explicit.

Preferred structure:

- feature UI/components: `frontend/src/features/<feature>/**`
- feature API client: `frontend/src/features/<feature>/api.ts`
- feature local types: `frontend/src/features/<feature>/types.ts`
- shared frontend utilities: `frontend/src/core/**`
- route-level composition: `frontend/src/pages/**`

Rules:

- Do not put large fetch blocks directly in page components.
- Do not duplicate API calls across pages; add or reuse a feature API client.
- Do not turn `TemplatesPage.tsx`, `ControlPage.tsx`, or `EditorPage.tsx` back
  into large mixed-responsibility modules.
- Keep editor state separate from control/rundown state.
- Keep renderer/timeline engine changes separate from normal UI changes.
- Prefer small feature components over broad page rewrites.

If a page grows because of new behavior, extract the behavior into the owning
feature directory instead of adding another large inline block.
